a hierarchical structure of truth.

01:14:05.920 --> 01:14:12.920
After all, there have been people, for example, Kripke, who, as were brought down, even for

01:14:13.240 --> 01:14:19.120
a formalized language, the truth predicates into the language and showed how you could

01:14:19.120 --> 01:14:23.480
do that consistently simply by having truth value gaps.

01:14:23.480 --> 01:14:28.440
It doesn't seem to me, as I say, an unequivocal verdict that Tarski showed that there was

01:14:28.440 --> 01:14:30.120
a hierarchy of truth predicates.

01:14:30.520 --> 01:14:35.120
No, I think not, and I don't think that Tarski would have said so either.

01:14:35.120 --> 01:14:36.840
I certainly prefer Tarski's.

01:14:36.840 --> 01:14:37.840
It's more elegant.

01:14:37.840 --> 01:14:43.840
It enables us to adhere to our standard, you might say, neoclassical logic, which has the

01:14:46.240 --> 01:14:53.240
virtue of simplicity and being so thoroughly understood, but certainly truth value gaps

01:14:53.240 --> 01:14:58.240
could accomplish the same thing.

01:14:58.240 --> 01:15:05.240
I think Kripke's proposal comes out rather less convenient by a good deal, and I would

